question: The government of Maharashtra renamed which of the following airports as Chhatrapati Sambhaji Maharaj Airport?
explanation: Aurangabad Airport was renamed as Chhatrapati Sambhaji Maharaj Airport by the government of Maharashtra. Previously renamed the airport of Maharashtra are Mumbai airport as Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj Airport and Kolhapur airport as Chhatrapati Rajaram Maharaj Airport.
